<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-130] ShiroFilter does not work with proxied security manager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-130</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;ShiroFilter.isHttpSessions()&lt;/tt&gt; method does an &lt;tt&gt;instanceof&lt;/tt&gt; check on the security manager, checking whether it&apos;s an instance of &lt;tt&gt;DefaultWebSecurityManager&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t work when the security manager is a JDK proxy to a &lt;tt&gt;DefaultWebSecurityManager&lt;/tt&gt; because the proxy implements the &lt;tt&gt;SecurityManager&lt;/tt&gt; interface, which doesn&apos;t have the &lt;tt&gt;isHttpSessions()&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps we should have a &lt;tt&gt;WebSecurityManager&lt;/tt&gt; interface with the &lt;tt&gt;isHttpSessions()&lt;/tt&gt; method defined on it?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
